{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> θερμός</b>, ή, όν <br /> (but θερμὸς ἀϋτμή [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “hymnus ad Mercurium” 110, 8th-7th c.BC: Hesiodus Epicus “Theogonia” 696)\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]: (θέρω):— <b>hot</b>, θ. λοετρά [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 14.6, compare 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 8.249; θ. λουτρά 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “O.” 12.19, 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Trachiniae” 634 (Lyric poetry), 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Leges” 761c, etc.; δάκρυα 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 19.362 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; of water, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"[prev. work] 388 \">Refs</a>]; of glowing wood,[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 9.388; θ. καύματα 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 3.104 (_superlative_)\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ἦν ἄρα πυρὸς ἕτερα -ότερα [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Equites” 382 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: frequently in <i>Attic dialect</i>, of <b>hot</b> meals or drinks, Telecl[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] 1.8,32, 5th c.BC: Pherecrates Comicus 130.8, etc. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; of blood, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Oedipus Coloneus” 622, “Aj.” 1411 (_anapaest meter_); -οτάταν αἱμάδα [prev. author] “Ph.” 696 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; of fever, θ. νόσοι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “P.” 3.66 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; θ. σῶμα <b>feverish</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 2.49. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> <i>metaphorically</i>, <b>hot-headed, hasty</b>, frequently of persons, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Septem contra Thebas” 603, “Eu.” 560 (Lyric poetry), 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Vespae” 918, etc.; θ. καὶ ἀνδρεῖος 5th c.BC: Antipho Orator 2.4.5 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; of actions, πολλὰ καὶ θ. μοχθήσας [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Trachiniae” 1046; θ. ἔργον 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Plutus” 415; δρᾶν τι νεανικὸν καὶ θ. 4th c.BC: Amphis Comicus 33.10; θ. ἐπὶ ψυχροῖσι καρδίαν ἔχεις 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Antigone” 88; θ. πόθος “Anthologia Graeca” 5.114 (1st c.BC: Philodemus Gadarensis Epigrammaticus); φάρμακον 4th c.AD: Alciphro Epistolographus 1.37 (_comparative_)\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: with <i>infinitive</i>, θερμότερος ἐπιχειρεῖν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Antipho Orator 2.1.7 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: <i>superlative</i>, ὦ θερμόταται γυναῖκες [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Thesmophoriazusae” 735. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.2</b></Level3> <b>still warm, fresh</b>, ἴχνη[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “Anthologia Graeca” 9.371\">Refs</a>]; ἀτυχήματα [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus 2.798f; θ. κακά, opposed to ἕωλα, [prev. work]517f; γάμοι θ. καὶ ἴσως αὔριον 2nd-3rd c.AD: Philostratus Sophista “Vita Apollonii” 4.25. \">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__III</b></Level2> τὸ θ.,= θερμότης, <b>heat</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 1.142, 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Cratylus” 413c, etc. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__III.2</b></Level3> θ. (i.e. ὕδωρ), τό, <b>hot water</b>, θερμῷ λοῦσθαι, βάπτειν, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Nubes” 1044, “Ec.” 216; θερμῷ κεκραμένος οἶνος 2nd c.AD: Galenus Medicus 11.56 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; also, <b>hot drink</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Arrianus Historicus “Epicteti Dissertationes” 1.13.2. \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__III.3</b></Level3> θερμόν, τό, <b>grace, favour</b>, θ. εὑρεῖν ἐν ἐρήμῳ [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" LXX.Jer.38(31).2. \">LXX</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__III.4</b></Level3> τὰ θ. (i.e. χωρία) [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 4.29 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; but (i.e. λουτρά), <b>hot springs</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Historia Graeca (Hellenica)” 4.5.3; τὰ θ. τοῦ Ἡρακλέους 1st c.BC-1st c.AD: Strabo Geographus 9.4.2. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__IV</b></Level2> <i>adverb</i> <b>-μῶς</b>[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Euthydemus” 284e \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: <i>comparative</i> -ότερον, ἔχειν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Eubulus Comicus 7.1 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]: <i>neuter</i> <i>plural</i> as <i>adverb</i>, θερμὰ θερμὰ πηδῶσαι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 3rd c.BC: Herodas Mimographus 4.61. \">Refs 3rd c.BC+</a>]","strongNumber":"G7661","accentedUnicode":"θερμός","shortDef":"hot","mediumDef":"hot","stepGloss":"hot","stepTransliteration":"thermos","count":0,"_step_Type":"word"}]}